**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I am making a version of rules_s3/rules_gcs that works with azure blob storage. Although it just uses an http interface the ability to pull down everything in a given bucket and version it via json is really nice for tests although you could likely put a messy version of this together with ctx.download.

One open question provided you would be willing to accept this change upstream would be if the `"x-ms-version": "2020-04-08"` header should also be added. It is not part of auth but is required for any calls to Azure I have found out. For now I baked it directly into the rules_abs code.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Right now I am using an ugly but workable solution that just uses the az cli interface to pull a token for me.

```
#!/bin/bash

access_token=$(az account get-access-token --resource https://storage.azure.com/ --query accessToken -o tsv)

json_output=$(cat <<EOF
{
  "headers": {
    "Authorization": ["Bearer $access_token"]
  }
}
EOF
)

echo "$json_output"
```

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
just keep using my ugly solution.

